==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Murderous
<hw>Mur"der*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to murder; characterized by, or causing, murder or bloodshed; having the
purpose or quality of murder; bloody; sanguinary; <as>as, the
<ex>murderous</ex> king; <ex>murderous</ex> rapine; <ex>murderous</ex>
intent; a <ex>murderous</ex> assault.</as></def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Murderous</xex> coward.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Mur"der*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Bloody; sanguinary; bloodguilty; bloodthirsty;
fell; savage; cruel.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murdress</ent>⟦br⟧
